Tammy Petersen, News24(File, iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Three men who robbed a store in a Cape Town shopping mall and killed a security guard are still at large, Western Cape police said on Thursday.The trio hit the Imariki Centre in Philippi on Wednesday afternoon at 17:00.Police spokesperson Captain FC Van Wyk said murder and business robbery cases were under investigation.The suspects are understood to have gunned down the guard, before making their way into a shop where they demanded money."They fled the scene with an undisclosed amount cash, and on their way out, hijacked a local taxi [escaping in the] Toyota Avanza," Van Wyk said.No one had been arrested, Van Wyk confirmed.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.